    • Method Detail

      • quesEmpty

        public void quesEmpty(ObjectQueue que,
             java.io.PrintWriter writer)
        Runs when the Job list has been emptied and empties the remaining Queues. Checks if the job is completed. If not, checks if there is remaining Quantum time. If not, moves into a lower level Queue.
        Parameters:
        que - Takes in the Queue containing all of the jobs.

      • notEmpty

        public void notEmpty(ObjectQueue que,
            java.io.PrintWriter writer)
        Runs when the Job list has not been emptied and simulates everything until it is. Checks if there is a new Job to add. Also, checks to see if the system already has a job on the Queue.
        Parameters:
        que - Takes in the Queue containing all of the jobs.

      • simBusy

        public void simBusy(java.io.PrintWriter writer)
        Runs when the Simulation's busy flag is set to true. Checks if the Job is over. If not, checks if the Quantum is over or if a New job has come to the system. If so, moves the Job to the next Lower Level Queue.

      • jobOver

        public void jobOver(java.io.PrintWriter writer)
        Runs when the job has completed. Clears the CPU so that there will be no conflicts when the next job is loaded. Sets the CPU busy flag to false.
